runs.comm: a hint of an appeal, full and swinging in, but nothing doing from the umpire. That would have missed leg
well, that's just rubbish. Short and flies off a rock-hard pitch, beating a diving Ramdin down the leg-side
outside off stump this time, much better. Driven into the off side with a flourish from the purposeful Prior
big stride but not a lot of impact. Dribbles into the off side
tucked up by one that nips back and leaps off the rock-hard track. Much better line and length now
slower ball, and it swings almost as much as Prior, who nearly carried himself off his feet as he pursued that one. But it was too wide
tighter line again, jabs off the splice. Very good carry on this pitch, rewarding those who frnd that awkward length
big mow outside off stump, under-edged into the crease and away to the keeper
good first ball, good line and length, and a hint of movement too
on the spot again, and Cook can't get that away
slightly shorter delivery, but Cook can't connect properly and that dribbles out to mid-on
turned into the leg-side. "That's a confused brain," says Cook's fellow Essex boy, Nasser Hussain. a touch harsh after seven balls, but there you go
eight balls, and already Cook's inclusion is being questioned. Another dot-ball piles on the pressure
ooh, that'll help. A touch wider, and walloped over point for England's first boundary off the bat
big stride down the pitch, but not timed. Prior is back to his pinch-hitting role for this match
lovely strike! Big stride and that's mown over the covers. Took the aerial route, and took it well
turned round the corner
a flat-batted belt straight back over the bowler! Wonderful free swinging, and England are up and running
that's absolutely clobbered. Up, up and away over cow corner, and suddenly the floodgates are opening
a swish and a miss outside off stump. Prior tried to cut but a bit of extra bounce. Still, a valuable over
lovely cricket, a free-swinging strike through the covers, and a great stop by Samuels in the covers
purposeful strike again, but can't quite connect
looked like it was going to go all the way for a moment or two, but cut off on the backward-point boundary. Another clean strike
a belter of a pitch, and Prior helps himself with another full swing through the line. The front leg was well out of the way, and that fizzed through the covers
squawked appeal, but Prior was so far down the pitch he was almost able to shake the hand of the umpire. He carries on in that vein to complete a single
canny play from Cook, uses the pace and opens the face. It ain't all about boundaries (just mostly)
a hint too short, and heaved through midwicket. Not quite gauged the pace though, although good running almost brings two
the lack of pace does the trick. Cook picked the length but not the speed, and tried to smear this over midwicket. Instead he got a leading edge, and Dwayne Bravo took a fine swirling chance at point
clipped off the toes, scampered round at midwicket
oops, nearly a mix-up as the two batsmen ball-watch and all but collide
that's a magnificent strike, got right underneath the ball and scooped it up and away into the stands at backward-square leg
slower ball, and that's scooped straight up into the air! Pace is bunk, is the message from this match
in the slot and defended first-up
a little bit of width, and that's a slightly nervy steer wide of the slips. KP is off the mark
steps across his crease and nurdles into the leg-side.
another couple, into the leg-side. That'll help calm the nerves
straight and just back of a length, pushed down the ground
just strays onto the pads, but that's clipped away gratefully, rather than heaved away dismissively. A tidy over
strays onto the pads again, and worked away. The West Indians have done their homework against Trott. Straight and straighter is what they want. Apparently
no such issues for KP. He just pushes this one down the ground to long-on
just outside the off stump. Defended and a scampered single as the ball bobbles into the off side
big swing-and-a-miss from Pietersen. Smith throws his hands up in something approaching despair
clipped into the leg-side again. Dare we say this game has gone a little flat for the moment?
turned into the deep yet again, and another tidy over
width again, and steered down to deep backward-point. No fireworks just yet
thumped. That's Pietersen's "go-to" shot, as Nasser Hussain puts it. A big stride and biffed through the covers
even better. Hoisted over midwicket, and that's two in two balls. Suddenly England have their tempo back
misses out this time with another off-side swing. Third man hurtles up to take a shy, but Pietersen is home

full and straight, and that's gone! Tried to flick that through the leg side, but played all around it and lost his leg stump. A tough situation in which to make a debut, but at least he's off the mark. More chances will come this week, I'm sure
confident stride, and that's pushed away to cover without any great timing
another swing, but can't beat the ring on the leg-side
full and yorker length, slower ball. Pushed down the ground
tails in towards the leg stump. A mistimed clump from Pietersen brings another single to long-on
that's the skipper's signature shot, a firm clip over the infield, and bobbles away for a welcome boundary
absolutely no pace to work with, and that's excellent bowling again. Full and straight
another dot ball to finish, and this is a fine spell from West Indies' middle-over bowlers
ouch! Pietersen is run out, and looked like he had done himself a serious damage when he leapt into the crease. Almost over-stretched his knee, but was able to walk off without much problem
cracked off the back foot
drifting down the leg-side - too straight, and Collingwood nudges it further to leg
Shah guides this, elegantly and deftly, down to third man
turned into the leg side to keep the strike
drifting onto his pads, Shah clips it - nothing more than a clip - to deep midwicket
down on one knee, Collingwood sweeps it down to fine leg but without really timing it
a full toss which takes the rabbits-in-the-headlights-Shah by surprise, the ball bobbling off his pads out to cover
punched down to long-off for a single
oh and he's got him! Shah was late onto that, trapped in front - they scamper through for a single and the umpire, belatedly, raises his finger
very well bowled indeed, the batsman clumping this back to the bowler without timing
Collingwood chips this over the top but just for a single. As ever.
nudged off his legs, but England need more than the odd nudge and nurdle
deftly played by Collingwood, a premeditated reverse sweep down to third man. DJ Sammy rocks a good tune, but he can't chase that down
a wide down the leg side
pushed to midwicket
down the leg side it's pushed down to fine leg
another pointless push for a single
a little too short but Sammy gets away with it, Collingwood trying to pull this but can't time it
that is a dreadful, sad little stroke, patting this wide ball straight to Morton at short third-man
Yardy nudges this down the ground
Collingwood skips down the pitch and punches it to long-on for a single. Oh in fact they get two, very well run
pulled to deep midwicket who takes it on the bounce
Yardy tries to clump this through midwicket but, pathetically, the ball barely gets off the cut strip and Sammy fields
that's more like it, Collingwood grasping the initiative: down the wicket, he swings this over long-on for a huge six
neatly cracked off the front foot square of the wicket, but they only get two
and he tries to reverse sweep this, Collingwood, but it's much, much quicker and clips his pad, the ball racing down to fine-leg for four
a leading edge to mid-off
shovelled (what a wonderful word that is) out to cover
neatly nudged to deep midwicket for two more
somehow, Yardy is beaten for pace here, trying to pull this into the stands but he scoops it just short of mid-on
very well bowled, spearing into his pads and Collingwood digs it out - digs it out with class and panache, too
a slower ball which Collingwood tries to sweep but mistimes it; Rampaul is gazelle-like down at fine-leg
Yardy stands tall and plays this along the ground
powered through midwicket, but all along the ground
neatly steered out out to, well, a deep point I suppose you could say
that's got snow on it: Collingwood skips down the pitch one more and skies this miles, miles in the air...and it's got enough legs on it to take it for six. Super shot
sponged out to cover
short, Yardy again throws the kitchen sink at it, but the sink is clearly made of cake, or something weak, as the ball bobbles out like a limp lettuce to cover
ooh well played, cutting this down to third man
oh hello, that's massive. Collingwood's up for the challenge - smacking this over the bowler's head into the stands, and a drunken member drops it
carved out to deep point
very well bowled indeed, swinging into Yardy's blockhole who clumps it to mid-off

swinging into Collingwood who does a Steve Waugh and cracks it over midwicket, but he hasn't middled it - Powell is the man out at deep midwicket but he can't get there in time, his hands crossing over eachother as though impersonating my Mum trying to party
ooh that's out. Ooh, no it's not - very close indeed, swinging into the batsman who's rapped on the pads
turned around the corner
bang, a flat four to long-on's left. Powerfully struck
a full toss, and he helps it over fine-leg for...six! Brilliant stroke. Collingwood's up for it
Yardy's hit a four! Again he put every ounce of energy into the stroke, the ball wallowing its way down the ground and it's just got enough on it to go for four
Yardy's awake now! He pulls this through midwicket for four more
excellent ball, straight and full; Yardy can't do anything with it, pushing it out to cover
a full toss which takes Collingwood by surprise, pushed to midwicket
uppercut down to third man who does really well to save four
in the blockhole, Collingwood just stands tall and hammers it down the ground for four
full, straight, Yardy doesn't know what's going on, hammering it into his pads and they scamper for a single. Rampaul tries to throw down the stumps but misses by a country mile
sponged down to third man for two
oh well bowled, Yardy steps outside leg but Rampaul sends it wide of the off stump. Very clever, very alert
Yardy does a little jig to try and put Rampaul off, but he can only slash it off an inside edge to midwicket
Collingwood steps down the pitch, Rampaul simply drops it a touch shorter and it swings past Collingwood's flashing blade. Brilliant bowling
again, fabulous ball which is too full for Collingwood to do anything with, clumping it through midwicket
full, well bowled, Yardy drives it down to long-off
mistimed to mid-off; Collingwood's quick between the wickets but he's going to be short of his ground here. In comes the throw, and the stumps are broken...but replays show he's safe
another non-boundary, Collingwood flinging it over midwicket without timing
a slower ball which completely foxes Yardy, trying to slash this outside off but missing it
bashed down the ground for a couple. Collingwood races back, but the throw from Dwayne Smith is quick and accurate, replays confirming Collingwood's fate
down the leg side Broad clips it to fine leg
